{"cursor":"30746","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n'Self-control' is the ability to control one's emotions, behavior, and desires\nin order to obtain some reward, or avoid some punishment. Presumably, some\n(smaller) reward or punishment is operating in the short term which precludes,\nor reduces, the later reward or punishment. In psychology it is sometimes called\nself-regulation. Exerting self-control through the executive functions in\ndecision making is held in some theories to deplete one's ability to do so in\nthe future.\n","linknr":347,"url":"Self-control","recorded":1362477626,"links":28,"instances":["book","mood","emotion"],"pdf":["http://www.apa.org/pubs/journals/releases/psp945883.pdf","http://www.apa.org/pubs/journals/releases/psp945883.pdf"],"categories":["Motivation","Social psychology","Self","Autonomy","Virtue"],"headings":["In behavior analysis","Self-control research","As a limited resource","In quality of life","Impulse control","Skinner's survey of self-control techniques","See also","References"],"image":["//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["desire","emotion"],["depression","mood"],["verbal_behavior","book"]],"members":["verbal_behavior","depression","desire"],"related":["Emotion","Behavior","Desire_(emotion)","Psychology","Executive_functions","Decision_making","Ego_depletion","Reinforcement","Token_economy","Impulsiveness","Functional_imaging","Dorsolateral_prefrontal_cortex","Frontal_lobe","Premotor_cortex","Amygdala","Alexandra_W._Logue","Cassandra_B._Whyte","Locus_of_control","Glucose","Roy_Baumeister","Empirical_evidence","Walter_Mischel","Marshmallow","Sociotropy","Depression_(mood)","Impulse_control","ADHD","Antisocial_Personality_Disorder","Borderline_Personality_Disorder","Substance_dependence","B.F._Skinner","Token_econo